        "id": 1004035
      },
      "writtenOn": "2010-07-14T11:40:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This property was added during development to validate that BluetoothHandsfree behavior is the same with/without the virtual-call changes i.e. the state-machine minus the virtual-call states did not break anything and cellular call handling behaved as before.\n\nNow we have confidence on the feature. I will remove this property and leave it enabled by default.",
      "parentUuid": "AAAA0n//9/8\u003d",
      "revId": "5220be0794449ba6f66cc1c813e72c6a75694f1d",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "AAAA0n//9/0\u003d",
        "filename": "src/com/android/phone/BluetoothHandsfree.java",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 164,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000635
      },
      "writtenOn": "2010-07-13T03:30:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Do we need so many states ? We just need to distinguish if a SCO or a Virtual Voice Call is active, right ?",
      "revId": "5220be0794449ba6f66cc1c813e72c6a75694f1d",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "AAAA1H///zQ\u003d",
        "filename": "src/com/android/phone/BluetoothHandsfree.java",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 164,
      "author": {
        "id": 1004035
      },
      "writtenOn": "2010-07-14T11:40:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In the common case, you are right that we only need to know whether SCO/Virtual-Call is active; whereas there are several race conditions possible and these states will ensure proper behavior. Here are a couple of instances:\n\nThe call_setup state is needed as we could be in call_setup when an virtual-call request is received, in which case the virtual call should be rejected. \n\nThe call_transfer state is needed especially when the handsfree is attempting to transfer the virtual call back to the handsfree device from the phone. The application needs to know this event as it can decide whether to play the audio locally or terminate the virtual call. If the application decides to do the latter and sends a stopVirtualCall then BluetoothHandsfree needs to know that a virtual call is in progress, but there is no SCO connection as the call has been transferred.",
      "parentUuid": "AAAA0n//9/0\u003d",
      "revId": "5220be0794449ba6f66cc1c813e72c6a75694f1d",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "AAAA1H///wQ\u003d",
        "filename": "src/com/android/phone/BluetoothHandsfree.java",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 164,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000635
      },
      "writtenOn": "2010-07-14T17:45:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "For the first case:\nThere is mForground / mBackground / mRinging call - that we can use to check if there is a call already in progress. I think there is some utility function in PhoneUtils too.\n\nFor the second case:\n   mConnectedSco - will tell us if there is SCO connection present or not.\n\nI agree there are race conditions, but I believe we can solve all of them without adding new states. Think about it, else we can have a call to discuss this.",
      "parentUuid": "AAAA1H///zQ\u003d",
      "revId": "5220be0794449ba6f66cc1c813e72c6a75694f1d",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "AAAA1H///jw\u003d",
