      "writtenOn": "2010-07-15T11:33:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "mConnectedSco is common to both cellular-call and virtual-call and hence cannot be used to differentiate, same issue with mOutgoingSco.\n\nThese states are not adding any complexity, but only guide the appropriate action. As per your suggestion, once we move the state checks into a function I think it should be fine. \n\nDo you have any specific concerns with these states?",
      "parentUuid": "AAAA1H///wQ\u003d",
      "revId": "5220be0794449ba6f66cc1c813e72c6a75694f1d",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
